text: The Beebe House is located in Platteville, Wisconsin. It is Victorian Gothic in style. With ==History== William Beebe served in the Union Army during the American Civil War, reaching the rank of captain. He would also become Mayor of Platteville. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Wisconsin Category:National Register of Historic Places in Grant County, Wisconsin Category:Houses in Grant County, Wisconsin Category:Gothic Revival architecture in Wisconsin Category:Brick buildings and structures Category:Houses completed in 1870
title: Beebe House (Platteville, Wisconsin)
